```csharp
// v3: Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj, out var typed);
// v4: var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj);
```

The behavior is identical â€” it asserts the type and gives you the cast value. Only the syntax changed.
